widgets_values: Un-bypass this group to use the override image instead of the one generated in the previous group.
Adjust Length of video, and also how many times to scroll the frame via the X and Y axis (e.g. 2 = scroll 2 images per animation cycle)
You can tweak the parameters on the following depthflow motion nodes to change the resulting animation. See the guide page for this workflow for a link to depthflow custom nodes documentation.

Use this group to generate and upscale the initial seamless tiling image. I recommend generating square images (aspect ratio 1) for best results.
I use zavychromaxl model as the base checkpoint and then add in additional loras such as TileMapStyle_v1.

nodes.title: Negative Prompt

widgets_values:
Adjust the output FPS if desired. Tiling mode should be left on "repeat".
Adjust edge_fix to add more or less padding around objects in the depthmap.

You can lower or increase the 'largest_size' parameter to make the largest side of the resulting depthmap scale accordingly. 
Lower the value if you get OOM errors.
